overview.en: INF is a blockchain-based storage application that allows users to encrypt and store a variety of alphanumeric data on a decentralized network. The user data is securely stored on a peer-to-peer network (IPFS) which also ensures that it is only accessible to the designated recipient upon a predetermined inactivity trigger. Examples of user data that can be stored in our secured environment are: passwords, wallet files, private keys, JSON files, UTC files, keystore files, mnemonic phrases, recovery seeds and even short text messages.
overview.zh: INF是一种基于区块链的存储应用程序，允许用户在去中心化的网络上加密和存储各种字母数字数据。用户数据被安全地存储在P2P网络（IPFS）上，该P2P网络还确保仅在预定的静态触发时它才能被指定的接收者访问。在我们的安全环境中可以存储的用户数据有：密码，钱包文件，私钥，JSON文件，UTC文件，密钥库文件，助记短语，恢复种子甚至短文本消息。
